Cape Town – Muizenberg police have appealed to the public to help them find Mandla Mhimhi, who is missing. The 29-year-old was reported missing on March 18 in Rasta Street. His brother last saw him on March 17 around 5pm. He is described as of average build and about 1.6m tall, with short black hair, brown skinned with brown eyes and a black beard. Mhimhi, who is mentally unstable, was believed to be in a green Puma jacket. Anyone with information on Mhimhi’s whereabouts can contact investigating officer Siyabulela Zazini on 021 787 9000/14/15 or 072 934 7219, alternatively Crime Stop on 08600 10111 or SMS Crime Line on 32211. Meanwhile, two suspects have been arrested for allegedly hijacking a vehicle in Kuyasa, Khayelitsha, yesterday. They were arrested after police officers received a complaint about the hijacking of a white Volkswagen Polo TSI. “The suspects, aged 21 and 28, were arrested with two imitation firearms in their possession, of which one was loaded with three rounds of ammunition,” said police spokesperson FC van Wyk. They are expected to appear in the Khayelitsha Magistrate’s Court. Cape Times